pective, I believe there are=C2=A0some possibility of corruption in the tea=
chings of almost all masters starting from Jesus to Buddha to Shanakara to =
Guru Nanak to Chaitanya to Vivekanada to=C2=A0Aurobindo . Corruptions not i=
n the teaching per se=C2=A0but corruption arising out of misinterpretation =
of the words over time. One cannot really blame them for this because it is=
 almost impossible to forsee what turn of events lead to what kind of minds=
ets which can make their statements/advises defuct or even dangerous over t=
ime.
=C2=A0
